-- Peru Stocks: Casa Grande, Minsur, Pomalca, Relapasa
-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 2012-03-16T21:29:30Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-16/peruvian-stocks-austral-el-brocal-panoro-relapasa.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses
and share prices are as of 3:10 p.m. Lima time.  The  Lima General Index (IGBVL)  fell 0.1 percent to 22,962.52. The
 MSCI (MXPECAPD)  All Peru Capped Index climbed 0.5 percent to 2,885.52.  Refineria la Pampilla SA  (RELAPAC1 PE), a unit of Repsol
YPF SA, rose 1.9 percent to 1.06 soles after crude gained in  New
York .  Empresa Agroindustrial Pomalca SA (POM\C)  (POMALCC1 PE), a sugar
producer, advanced 1.8 percent to 56 centimos after sugar rose
earlier in New York.  Casa Grande (CASAGRC1)  (CASAGRC1 PE), Peru’s largest sugar producer
and a unit of Gloria SA, climbed 1.3 percent to 17.80 soles.  Minsur SA (MINSURI1)  (MINSURI1 PE), the world’s fourth-largest tin
producer, fell 1.3 percent to 3.05 soles after futures declined
in London, said Arlen Lahura, a trader at Lima-based brokerage
Coril SAB.  Volcan Cia. Minera SAA (VCM\B)  (VOLCABC1 PE), Peru’s largest zinc
producer, slid 2.2 percent to 3.50 soles after zinc dropped for
the second session in three in  London .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alex Emery in Lima at 
 aemery1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
